From da6b38403b8610edf51060a6f1eec8746d058e3b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Neal Gompa <ngompa@kde.org>
Date: Tue, 25 Nov 2025 18:29:55 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] Add support for installing PAM configuration

This allows us to canonically maintain the PAM configuration for
Plasma Login Manager with the project code and ensure the configuration
gets updated as the code changes.

It is also possible to not install configuration for development
purposes and also if custom PAM configuration is being shipped
instead.

The initial PAM configuration files added are for Fedora Linux and
SUSE Linux distributions.
---
